<HEADLINE>
NTU AZALEA FESTIVAL OPENS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March  4 (CNA) 03/04/07  21:01:06 (By Y.L. Kao)
</P>
<P>
An annual Azalea Festival opened at National Taiwan University
(NTU) Sunday and will continue until the end of March as part of
the Taipei Art Festival.
</P>
<P>
NTU President Lee Si-chen announced the opening of the festival
at a ceremony held in front of the university's main gate.
</P>
<P>
Asustek Chairman Johnny Shih, an outstanding NTU alumnus, and
Chang Han-tung, a representative of the NTU Alumni Association,
were also present at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Lee said that in connection with the festival, the NTU will hold
aseries of activities in March, including an exposition featuring
the university's 54 departments and performances to be staged by
some 100 student groups at the NTU Sports Center March 17-18.
</P>
<P>
In addition, an Azalea Festival Illusion Show integrating science
and art will open March 17 at the NTU Main Library and continue
for a month, with the aim of allowing the audience to personally
experience and interacting with intriguing illusions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile several museums run by the NTU will open to the public
during the period, Lee added, inviting the public to enjoy all of
the activities, as well as appreciating a sea of colorful azaleas
in full bloom along Coconut Tree Boulevard on the NTU campus. The
NTU will offer outdoor-lighting  at some sites on campus to
facilitate flower-viewing, he added.
</P>
